PSCU @PeopleDailyKe Somali Prime Minister Hassan Ali Khaire has thanked Kenya for being Somalia’s number one strategic partner in the ongoing transformation of the country. Khaire said the strong partnership between the two countries is good for the stability and progress of the East African region. He spoke on Tuesday evening at State House, Nairobi, when he delivered Somalia President Mohammed Abdullahi Mohamed’s goodwill and condolence message to President Uhuru Kenyatta following the recent terrorist attack at 14 Riverside Drive. Khaire said his country appreciates the key role Kenya has played in stabilising and reconstructing the Horn of Africa nation. “We request you to continue leading in the efforts of reconstructing our nation,” he said. He assured Uhuru that Somalia stands in solidarity with the country in the fight against terrorism and violent extremism. Khaire said Somalia is striving to build upon the stability brought by Amisom peacekeeping mission. Uhuru expressed delight to learn Somalia is on a positive trajectory economically, socially and in its relations with global partners. “This is proof that Kenya’s efforts have not gone to waste.”